From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mesh-llm <mesh-llm@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Use DSA indexer graph for GLM_DSA decode

GLM_DSA loads the DSA/lightning-indexer tensors, but its normal decoder graph
was still aliased to the DeepSeek2 MLA graph. Route normal GLM_DSA decode
through the DeepSeek32 DSA graph so the native executor consumes the sparse
indexer path instead of silently running the dense MLA fallback.

The MTP graph remains on the existing DeepSeek2 MTP path until GLM-5.2
IndexShare/MTP parity is audited separately.
---
 src/models/models.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/models/models.h b/src/models/models.h
index f1a84e151..5fa220f03 100644
--- a/src/models/models.h
+++ b/src/models/models.h
@@ -1110,7 +1110,7 @@ struct llama_model_glm_dsa : public llama_model_base {
     void load_arch_hparams(llama_model_loader & ml) override;
     void load_arch_tensors(llama_model_loader & ml) override;
 
-    using graph = llama_model_deepseek2::graph;
+    using graph = llama_model_deepseek32::graph;
     using graph_mtp = llama_model_deepseek2::graph_mtp;
 
     std::unique_ptr<llm_graph_context> build_arch_graph(const llm_graph_params & params) const override;
-- 
